caption: Friendly staff, good food, great atmosphere
Love this eatery.
Its a full, bustling restaurant, all in one space with tables stuck close to one another because it really is delicious. Even servers are Italian :)
For decades this spot has delivered tasty fair with good service. I have been for lunch and dinner, with friends and on business. It's a little more expensive and worth it.
Everyone of us loved. Looking ahead to our subsequent go to both with own family or buddies. One of my favorite place.
I determined to propose this eating place to the whole group since our italian colleague can be leaving us and going returned to his domestic town
Sammy took great care of us and allowed us to enjoy such a romantic night. Would 100% recommend.
Absolutely wonderful. The service was great but the food....delicious. Everything is fresh and made to order and is served hot. If you haven't been here, you should.  Highly recommend.
The service is thoroughly professional. I look forward to sampling their more extensive (and expensive) dinner menu.

Great restaurant. Food was great here. Went for thanksgiving. Staff was very nice and accommodating. The outdoor area was nice too, only downside is that they need some music out there and a couple more heaters. The tent they have is awesome, but wind and cold air still finds its way thru. Overall, pizza was great, pasta was great too.
Great food, horrible server.
Great place for tasty Italian food. Service is consistently great.
Wonderful ambiance, quality delicious food, and attentive personable wait staff.

Bolognese pasta was the quality of a diner; at $23 no less! Beet salad was good. But wine by the glass was about 25% low on quantity. Last time I had Branzino that was tasteless and pricey. Sorry guys.

Me and my family had dinner. I ordered RISOTTO and the portion was smaller than my dog’s plate for dinner. So disappointed but other than that everybody was happy with their meal. We had miscommunication getting wines so we paid extra without knowing. It was not cool. Just make sure speak up for yourself sometimes when you are not happy.
Great Drag brunch on Sunday’s hosted by Chicago’s premier comedy Queen @Teriyaki. So much fun. Food is fantastic especially the calamari and you can’t beat the bottomless mimosas for $21. 5 stars!!!
Very beautiful restaurant with great food, wine, and service.
One of my preferred spots for tasty italian food. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
italian food, very delicious. Nice place to meet and catch up with family. I had a brother come into town and asked me to take him back here.
Ok location for delicious Italian food. definitely one of the best places in the area. the bill was fair for the quality of food. food is similar to a cafe in indianapolis i loved.
italian food, super satisfying. The food was super appetizing. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. The bill was reasonable.

Always a blast for brunch! I recommend it, their drag show is great. Food is delicious as well, they have a good mimosa deal and won’t rush you either. I strongly recommend this place if you’re in Chicago.
Top 10 places for a wonderful romantic dinner! The back patio is adorable but the food is the real winner here! Get everything and anything it all great! The Branzino is to die for!!!
Absolutely delicious. Great service. The back garden/patio is so pretty.
Good place for Italian food. Loved this place from the first taste. The service here is above par.
Fine spot for Italian food. Arrived at five, it wasn't busy. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers. The bill won't break you. Feeling here is similar to a cafe in San Jose I liked.
Great food and ambiance while on the patio
Food was average , at best , they really need to work on bringing the quality up . Service was excellent!!!
Great all around service, amazing cocktails and Italian food. If you can get a table on the back patio there is no place in Chicago much better.
Fantastic food. Danny is awesome
Great service and I had an amazing meal!

Never disappoints. Food is always amazing. The bar tenders have a ton of character making our time entertaining and a ton of laughs & our waitress Consuelo really made our whole dining experience top  notch. We really enjoyed celebrating here and will be back again regularly. The back patio is to die for! So pretty.

Such a beautiful & charming restaurant. The back patio transports you to somewhere in Europe, its delightful. The inside is true Chicago and the tiny bar area is so welcoming. The food is phenomenal! Everything we have had here has been delicious. They have a nice wine list and they make a super aperol spritz! Service is great and everyone is always very friendly. This restaurant is a little gem downtown, we love it!

I had my family visiting out of town and we decided to come here . Food was excellent, however service was even better . Our server Lougiee, what a great server, entertainer . The whole restaurant was taken cared of by him and his teammates . He ran the whole restaurant gracefully,  like one big party . Great personality, detailed service and fantastic suggestions . Future guests will be recommended to come here to see Lougiee. Thank you !
This place is amazing! Great atmosphere and great service! I ordered a tagliatelle pasta and a salmon tartar. Couldn't ask for a better night! Highly recommended!

This Italian restaurant has a delicious menu and friendly, accommodating staff. The decor and ambiance are pleasant and relaxing. My personal favorites are the lentil soup, and the orecchiette with sausage. Don't miss out!
Amazing place. Great experience. Highly recommend their squid ink.
The ambience is good, service was fast and prompt. Appetizers were good. Somehow the main course wasn't that great.
The service was great Small portions.

The bar area has a cozy atmosphere with a nice fireplace. The wine was good. The restaurant area atmosphere is nothing special. The food was ok- the gnocchi was an odd shape and was with tuna. That being said, I would return if they lowered the prices.
Nothing special. Nice staff and ambiance, the food is just meh.
The ambience and service we’re amazing! The food and wine was great! I love the wall Decour in the main dining room. Great to have dinner with parents!
Good food Cool Atmosphere  n Decor

Amazing food. Fantastic service. Reasonable prices. We visited later into the night when it was slower, and we loved chatting with the bartender. We ordered food, including dessert, and took another meal home. They brought us the to-go meal just as we were leaving. Perfect timing. Will definitely be back!
The food was really good and the healthy choices were very delicious. The 1 LB icecream cake did not disappoint!
Amazing wines! Guerrieri Celso Wine is my new favorite!

Beautiful scenery, wait staff very attentive. The only reason I take off a star is the food simply isn't worth the price. You pay for the environment and service. The food is good but now worth the cost of at minimum 25$ a plate
Nice little patio in the back, great food and good service
Went here for NYE, good atmosphere and quaint.
Cute atmosphere
It was as excellent as I expected, thank you.

Great food and atmosphere, friendly staff NB and clean tables. Dessert was the star, the veal was amazing, but would have been S+ with just lemon and salt. Didn't need the breading. All and all pretty dang good.

Excellent food and very professional service.
Amazing Italian.  Great service.

My friend and I had a really nice time eating at La Storia this Sunday. I had the porchetta and thought the lentils were cooked to perfection. There was really not much we would change about our experience.  I think both my friend and I would agree that our very favorite parts of the meal were the octopus and the gelato. I had actually never had octopus before, and don't care much for seafood in general. That being said, I thought the flavor was really amazing and my friend said it was the best octopus he's ever had! We had three types of gelato while we were there: vanilla, chocolate, and lemon. The lemon made with freshly squeezed lemons. You could tell that there is a lot of work put into it.  The venue was also lovely, I enjoyed reading about the murals in the packet I received upon request. My friend and I had a nice time matching the description to the depiction of each historical figure.  One thing I really liked personally was that I noticed the waiter gave detailed explanations of the food to not only my table, but also surrounding tables. I was really happy to see that the service seemed consistently good.  Overall I was very impressed!

Italian food in Chicago better be good, and this is no exception. Close enough to downtown to make it a good location for visits, while still being high quality food not marketed to tourists (*cough* rosebud).  Honestly, the pasta is simply amazing. There's no other way to put it. Everything is executed so well that it's just one of those restaurants that leaves you unable to point out a flaw.
So classy without being overbearing or stuffy. The gnocchi is FANTASTIC!

Booked a reservation using the restaurants website for March 4 (which is a Monday) nowhere on any website or google says that they change hours on Monday for winter/summer months. Come to find out it was closed. I even received a confirmation email with my reservation number. Terribly managed restaurant and will not support them again.
Good food, and even better service. The drinks taste wonderful.
Extremely High priced.   Although the food quality was good, a 20% reduction in food prices would invite us back.   Very cozy atmosphere.
A great place to go on a date. Great food , amazing ambience and lovely drinks. The dishes might look on the higher side but definitely worth it. I would love to go back again.
Great spot that gives you the authentic Italian family feel.  Lasagna was great
The most authentic Italian in ChiTown
It nice with good food and the service is very good Thank you

Reviews I had read had all been great, but I had a subpar experience here. The service was not good. The staff was not well versed on the menu and it felt like they were rushing us out of the restaurant.The portion sizes were small and dishes lacked flavor. Although the ambience is relatively nice, this restaurant is not worth it whatsoever. Save your money and go elsewhere.
Everything was great except Consuela never have me a single drink refill
The patio setting was beautiful with twinkling lights. The staff was friendly and attentive. The food was delicious.

Excellent service and food. We were a large group of 25. We had made reservations two weeks ahead of time and were set up to have a private room. Unfortunately, the reservations were made with the wrong contact number. When the reservations could not be confirmed the restaurant thought we were not coming. When 25 of us walked in unexpectedly at 8pm, the staff was incredibly gracious. They set everything up and got us seated quickly in private seating. The service was excellent the entire night for our whole group. For twenty-five people (most of us drinking wine) the price was more than reasonable. I highly recommend this restaurant. Bravo!! to the staff and chefs.

Something was definitely off about this restaurant. The wait service was lacking and inconsistent, and it seemed like the waiter was annoyed to have to serve our table. The restaurant was mostly empty at 8pm on a Saturday.  When we ordered a bottle of wine, he went away and then came back saying they had to go find it. Seemed odd to me that they couldn’t locate a medium priced bottle of Italian wine on their wine list.  The food was great, no complaints there. We ordered a number of pastas and a couple mains for the table to share.  They really need to adjust something with how they are waiting on the tables and perhaps find happier waiters. I’m not sure I’ll be back.
I live in Chicago since 2015, eat ~20 Italian restaurants, and haven't seen one (even the cheapest bars) with food of that terrible quality.
Great atmosphere and food

Great Italian traditional restaurant with a great personal touch. We sat on the patio and the night was beautiful. The wine was great, the music was perfect. We ordered the tasting chefs courses. The Tomato soup was the starter, it was great. We had whole wheat linguini. Then we finished with the chocolate mousse, the mousse was amazing, very think and very good. You can tell it was authentic and made fresh. Overall the service was good, fast and professional. The setting was cozy and wasn’t crazy busy on a Friday night around 9. Highly recommend, the chefs courses were only $28 which was super reasonable for the amount of food we ate. There is an amazing mural on the inside, must see,
The atmosphere, food, and service were excellent. The building is a restored Victorian house which adds to the whole experience.

I was scrolling through Seated and saw La Storia. This restaurant is one of my new Chicago favorites, and I've been to quite a few places!! Both the truffle gnocchi and the pumpkin ravioli were absolutely outstanding. The flavors were bold and well balanced, and the gnocchi melted in my mouth. In addition, the service was impeccable--our Italian waiter was friendly, asked if anyone was gluten free before serving the complementary bread, and the food came out in a timely manner. On top of it all, they have a beautiful outdoor patio, and it was a bit chilly in the evening, so they brought a space heater out and put it perfectly next to our tavle. Quite the exquisite evening--would definitely recommend!

Great atmosphere. The shrimps in the Cioppino my absolute favorite.
Horrible food and service
Good ambiance, great food. Will definitely return and recommend to friends and family.

My sister, her boyfriend, and I visited for my birthday dinner. We were hoping for a nice evening to celebrate but were soon disappointed. The atmosphere was nice, though our server seemed very frazzled, despite the restaurant not being too busy (there were several open tables, though I don't know how tables are assigned to severs so they may not have been his empty tables). When I asked about a potential substitution (I am a vegetarian and there was meat in the sauce of one dish), our server instantly directed me to other dishes instead of checking to see if a substitution was possible. I ordered the spaghetti he suggested, despite that not being what I wanted. Unfortunately, I regretted that once it came out. The presentation was lacking compared to the salads my sister and her boyfriend ordered, and I had to request parmesan cheese because someone had forgotten to add it, according to our server. The more I had, the more I regretted going out; I easily could have made the same thing at home with Ragu or Prego. My sister's boyfriend ordered meatballs that were burnt on the outside and raw in the centre. When we explained our disappointment to the manager, he very generously compensated part of our meal, but at that point we just wanted to leave. The salads and drinks my sister and her boyfriend ordered were good. I don't know if someone was having a bad day in the kitchen or if something else was going on, but hopefully it's sorted out soon. I expected more from a Michelin recommended restaurant, and I'm saddened at how disappointed I was with this meal. It made my birthday a little worse. I hope if you go your experience is better than mine.

Awesome restaurant! Great Italian atmosphere with excellent service. The food was amazing. The shrimps in the Cioppino were outstanding. Good for a date night but also for small groups. Large wine menu and a couple beers available. The Menu has pizza, a variety of starters pasta, seafood and meat. It was hard to decide what to eat because everything looked delicious. Can absolutely recommend this place.
Would not recommend.  Food was just ok and left hungry

I visited Chicago for the first time last week! It was a beautiful experience! I was shopping most of the afternoon and asked my husband to meet me at the restaurant (Dearborn Street). My hubby got there before me and was seated by the host (I think her name was Natalie) on the right wing of the restaurant which was dark and empty. When I got there about 20 mins later I asked for him at the front and they told me no one was there with the description I gave ( my husband is a black man 6 feet tall). So I decided to walk around and finally found him isolated by himself tucked away in a dark dingy corner where no one else was eating. The crazy thing was that he left wing was full of laughter, almost 10, 15 people dining.  I believe this was a case of discrimination. My husband was seated in an area where He was the only black man. Isolated. And removed from society. He was totally being hidden.  Great food and excellent drinks though! But the experience took me back 50 years almost reminded me of Rosa Parks. Sit at the back of the bus. Sit at the back of the restaurant. Treat your customers with equal rights to enjoy their dining experience with everyone else. The host was horrible. Our waitress was a lot better.

Great service but very poor menu list.Very expensive, bad food, little portions. Don waist your time and money there.

Excellent modern Italian food in a classic Chicago setting. Get cocktails at the bar for aperitivo before moving on to dinner with a great selection of Italian Wine. I was blown away by the back patio seating and the upstairs seating seemed impressive for quieter dining options.

Enjoyed a wonderful dinner in their well designed and comfortable space. Great menu options and can echo what others have said about the cauliflower and add the pastas were done just right. An experience I'd go back for- from the food to service.
unbelievable food. I love to cook. this is pure art
Food was great and wait staff excellent

I had high expectations based on reviews. So I decided to have my bf take me here for my bday. The waiter seemed to constantly up sell us and later when we asked for two more glasses of wine he must've chosen the most expensive glasses on the list. The food was mediocre for the price. Pork chop was dry flavorless. We expected something thick juicy. to accommodate they offered a side on the house. Again nothing great. It was not the meal I was expecting. The only great thing was the ambiance THAT was incredible. I love the mood and feel. Very romantic. We had the best spot in the house. Saved the evening.
Great food, ambience and service.  The caprese salad and the cauliflower were amazing as was the grilled octopus although the octopus was a very small serving

The caulliflower is phenomenal. Never enjoyed a vegetable so much. I had never had swordfish before and it was amazing, also took a bite of ravioli and wished I had a second stomach to eat more. Top notch decor, if it's not busy take a moment to inspect the detail on the mural.
